### Post-PR review inheritance (binding)

Detached **`coding-session`** ship chains reuse plan-and-deliver mechanics ÔÇö this wrapper does **not** own PR review-cycle steps. After **`create-pr`**, the inline **`pr-review`** / **`pr-review.mjs`** boundary from [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc ┬º Post-PR handoff](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc) applies unchanged. Do **not** restate the review procedure here; when the developer picks **`start-pr-review`**, load [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md) via [Post-create-pr handoff gate](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-create-pr-handoff-gate).

### Repo rules ship inheritance (binding)

Detached **`coding-session`** lanes execute canonical plan-and-deliver repo-rules behavior ÔÇö this wrapper does **not** duplicate reconcile or post-review rule-update steps. **Pre-PR:** [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` ┬º *Repo rules reconciliation (binding)*](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-binding) and [Repo rules reconciliation gate](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#repo-rules-reconciliation-gate) ÔÇö plan ┬º5 ÔåÆ **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** before ship cut-point. **Post-review:** when inline **`pr-review`** classifies **Rule-update required**, follow [Post-review repo rules handoff](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-review-repo-rules-handoff) after the disposition gate ÔÇö see [plan-and-deliver `pr-review/SKILL.md`](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/pr-review/SKILL.md).

**Parallel `hosting-repo-rules` fork (cross-ref only):** When product **`coding-session`** terminals carry **`repoRulesReconciliationStatus: pending`**, parent **`master-planner`** / **`phase-planner`** may fire-and-forget spawn **`hosting-repo-rules`** per canonical [plan-and-deliver `coding-session/SKILL.md` ┬º *Spawner spawn-detection outputs*](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#spawner-spawn-detection-outputs) and [plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc ┬º8 detached branches](.sedea/centers/research-and-development/missions/plan-and-deliver/plan.mdc). This wrapper inherits that contract ÔÇö **no duplicate spawn prose here**.

## Objectives

1. **Ad-hoc PRD intake** ÔÇö From a short change request, produce a developer-approved Ad-Hoc PRD under `.sedea/operations/.../docs/` via **`ad-hoc-prd`** (not full **`author-prd`**).

2. **Bounded Master Plan** ÔÇö Scaffold and draft a Master Plan with **`master-planner`**, compute complexity score; **reject** dispatches when overall score **> 20** (ÔëÑ 21) and recommend **`plan and deliver`**.

3. **PR breakdown only** ÔÇö On the Master Plan lane, run **`pr-breakdown`** inline only (no **`delivery-phases`** / **`phase-planner`**); allow **1ÔÇô6** PR rows; expand PR plans with **`new-plan`** + **`pr-plan`** inline.

4. **Standard implementation and ship** ÔÇö After inline **`pr-plan`** ┬º5c **Start coding session**, the **Master Plan child lane** emits ┬º5d **`AGENT_RUN_REQUEST_V1`** for **`coding-session`** (same contract as plan-and-deliver). Ship chain runs on the spawned **`coding-session`** lane: cut-point, deploy-walk, pre-pr-review, create-pr, pr-review, post-merge cleanup, optional plan-reconcile. **Forbidden:** redirecting ┬º5d spawn to the Squad Leader because the leader does not spawn ship skills from ┬º┬º1ÔÇô7.

5. **Squad Leader oversight** ÔÇö Leader lane runs planning spawns (┬º┬º1ÔÇô7), tracks planning ledger, and ┬º8 ship ledger via Mission Control host sync (same automation contract as plan-and-deliver ┬º8 when host supports this mission slug).

